To go from django-cms 2.3 to 3.0 these commands are required on every install:

Manually rename these table (poor migration from djangocms IMO):

DROP TABLE cmsplugin_groupphoto_groupphotoplugin;
DROP TABLE cmsplugin_launchpad_bugcountplugin;
DROP TABLE cmsplugin_brochure_brochureplugin;
ALTER TABLE cmsplugin_groupphotoplugin RENAME TO cmsplugin_groupphoto_groupphotoplugin;
ALTER TABLE cmsplugin_bugcountplugin RENAME TO cmsplugin_launchpad_bugcountplugin;
ALTER TABLE cmsplugin_brochureplugin RENAME TO cmsplugin_brochure_brochureplugin;

ALTER TABLE cmsplugin_latestnewsplugin RENAME TO cmsplugin_news_latestnewsplugin;
ALTER TABLE cmsplugin_pygmentsplugin RENAME TO cmsplugin_pygments_pygmentsplugin;

syncdb
migrate djangocms_text_ckeditor 0001 --fake
migrate

If this isn't done, admin won't be right:

collectstatic --noinput

This to fake person migrate:

migrate person 0001 --fake

reset resource

loaddata utils/datums/license.json
loaddata utils/datums/categories.json

Add RECAPTURE keys to local_settings.py

ISSUE: Live had a problem with django_file_file table, migration 0002 attempted to create a new column 'target' but it wasn't allowed to be NULL. Er.

Remove the old plugins:

cms delete_orphaned_plugins


